der, spring onions and carrot in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add sesame oil, reserved minced pork, egg, Chinese five spice, soy sauce, chilli (if using), salt and pepper then mix <b>30 sec\/\/speed 4<b> while stirring with spatula through hole in mixing bowl lid. Grease Varoma dish with oil."},{"content":"Using wet hands, form 1 heaped tablespoon of mixture into a golf ball sized ball and place in prepared Varoma dish. Repeat with remaining mixture to form 18 balls. Brush balls with water then set dish aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Vegetables and Noodles"},{"content":"Place stock cubes and water in mixing bowl then bring to the boil <b>8 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Place covered Varoma into position and steam <b>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, prepare carrot and courgette in ribbons, slice pepper and drain bamboo shoots. Mix together then transfer to Varoma tray."},{"content":"Insert Varoma tray then cover Varoma and steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Set Varoma aside."},{"content":"Place a large bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in noodles. Remove bowl then pour cooking water onto noodles and allow to stand until soft (approx. 3 minutes). Using tongs, transfer noodles to a serving dish and toss with steamed vegetables. Arrange meatballs on top and sprinkle with coriander. Serve warm with sauce of choice, such as soy sauce (see tip)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To give finished meatballs a crispy coating, finish off by frying in an oiled pan until lightly browned on all sides.","Drizzle dish with some of the fragrant cooking water instead of a sauce, if desired.<br>"],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h","4 portions"]}